y brown stream of cola pours out sideways in a smooth, ribbon-like line. The can is held in his hand against his shirt, the white “Coke” name clear on the red label. The stream stretches out from the can as though traveling through the room on its own, catching highlights like a dark, sparkling wave.\n\nThe woman reclines in profile, her head resting against the lounge chair’s white frame and black woven backing. Her hair moves slightly around her face, and she turns her attention toward the approaching drink. The cola stream passes through the elegant room, near a glass table with a metal vase of white flowers. Droplets or reflections glint around the surface, emphasizing the liquid’s motion.\n\nA small terrier-like dog with wiry white and gray fur sits on a cushioned sofa, wearing a red collar with a round tag. The dog looks alertly toward the action, ears perked. Elsewhere in the room, a black grand piano stands beside a small bench, with flowers on top and sheet music open on the music stand. The ribbon of cola passes in front of the open sheet music, making the pages flutter and bend as it moves by. The piano brand lettering is faintly visible on the front.\n\nThe Coke can appears again in the man’s hand, still tilted, with a few drops trailing from its opening. A hand places or steadies a tall empty glass on a tabletop beside a clear ice bucket filled with ice. The woman’s round sunglasses now rest nearby at the base of the glass, linking the setup to her. The cola stream continues across the pale wall like a thin, dark line, still suspended rather than spilling.\n\nThe woman lies back on the lounge chair, her blue-green swimsuit visible against the blue glow of the windows. A tall glass is then shown at an angle as the cola stream enters it. Ice inside the glass churns and flashes with bright reflections while the brown liquid swirls and rises, creating bubbles and foam near the top.\n\nFinally, the woman lifts the filled glass to her mouth. The drink is dark